HEADWORD: Archeus
<hw>Ar*che"us</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>arch⟦emac⟧us</ets>, Gr. <grk>'archai^os</grk> ancient, primeval,
fr. <grk>'archh`</grk> beginning. See <er>Archi-</er>,
<ets>pref</ets>.]</ety> <def>The vital principle or force which
(according to the Paracelsians) presides over the growth and
continuation of living beings; the <altname>anima mundi</altname> or
plastic power of the old philosophers.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

